<h1>Problem 173 - 2007 Hungary-Israel MO, P6 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(t \geq 3\) be a real number and assume the polynomial \(P(x)\) satisfies \[\left | P(k) - t^k \right | < 1\] for \(k = 0, 1, 2, \dots, n.\) Prove that the degree of \(P\) is at least \(n.\)</p>
